TRY TO CONTROL THE DRIFT

195
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:31,916
BY ONLY MANIPULATING THE GAS
PEDAL, LIKE YOU WOULD IN AN FR.

196
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,375
FULL ACCELERATION IS
THE ONLY WAY TO DRIFT

197
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:36,666
IN A FOUR-WHEEL-DRIVE.

198
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:40,708
THAT'S THE MOST DIFFICULT ASPECT
OF RACING IN A FOUR-WHEEL-DRIVE.

199
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:44,041
NO ONE WITH JUST MEDIOCRE SKILLS
CAN HANDLE A CAR AT FULL SPEED

200
00:12:44,125 --> 00:12:45,500
THROUGH A DRIFT.

201
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:50,666
BUT ONCE YOU'RE ABLE TO
MASTER THE TECHNIQUE,

202
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:51,916
YOU CAN TURN ANY CORNER

203
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:55,666
YOU COME UP ON AT
RIDICULOUSLY HIGH SPEEDS.

204
00:13:01,875 --> 00:13:05,333
I GUESS SEIJI DOES HAVE WHAT IT
TAKES TO KNOCK THIS KID OUT.

205
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:07,666
- ( tires screeching )

206
00:13:08,666 --> 00:13:10,958
BUT, WHY AM I FEELING
SO ON EDGE?

207
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,458
- ENTER AT TOP SPEED AND TURN
WITH FULL ACCELERATION.

208
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:24,875
IT'S A COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT MANEUVER

209
00:13:24,958 --> 00:13:26,666
THAN THE SLOW-ASSED CRAB TURN

210
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:30,208
THE EIGHT-SIX HAS TO DO.
NOW WATCH AND LEARN.

211
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:31,666
BUT I GUESS HE'D HAVE TO
BE SOMEWHAT CLOSE

212
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:33,166
TO SEE IT WITH HIS OWN EYES.

213
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:36,375
I DOUBT HE'S ANYWHERE NEAR ME.
I WONDER IF HE'S GIVEN UP.

214
00:13:39,666 --> 00:13:41,000
WHAT THE HELL?

215
00:13:46,041 --> 00:13:48,541
I DON'T GET IT!
HE'S RIGHT ON MY ASS!

216
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:52,875
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE? HOW WAS HE
ABLE TO KEEP UP WITH MY DRIFT?

217
00:13:52,958 --> 00:13:56,416
HE'S BETTER THAN I THOUGHT.
HUH. NOW THIS IS A RACE.

218
00:14:29,375 --> 00:14:32,333
- NOW I SEE. I WASN'T GETTIN'
IRRITATED BACK THERE

219
00:14:32,416 --> 00:14:34,291
BECAUSE HE WAS STOPPING
ME FROM THE SPEEDS

220
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:36,791
I WANTED ON THE STRAIGHTAWAYS.

221
00:14:36,875 --> 00:14:38,750
I THINK I KNEW
WHAT WAS BOTHERING ME

222
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:39,958
BACK WHEN I WAS FOLLOWING HIM,

223
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:42,791
BUT FOR SOME REASON
I KEPT IGNORING IT.

224
00:14:45,666 --> 00:14:49,583
I HATE TO ADMIT IT
BUT IT'S TRUE.

225
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:53,625
DAMMIT. I'M JUST NOT AS FAST
IN THE CORNERS AS HE IS!

226
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:02,625
- SO FAR, I'VE MANAGED
TO KEEP UP WITH HIS PACE.

227
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:11,541
- Seiji: THERE'S ONE
OTHER THING TOO.

228
00:15:11,625 --> 00:15:13,666
THE STRAIGHTAWAYS HERE
ARE SHORTER THAN NORMAL

229
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:15,375
SO THE SEPARATION IN
POWER BETWEEN US

230
00:15:15,458 --> 00:15:17,708
DOESN'T MAKE MUCH DIFFERENCE.

231
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:21,416
BUT JUST WAIT. WE'RE COMIN' UP
ON THE HIGH-SPEED SECTION,

232
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:25,250
AND ONCE WE DO, I'M GONNA BLOW
THIS EIGHT-SIX OUTTA THE WATER!

233
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:27,375
THEY'RE ABOUT TO SEE
SOME MAGIC!

234
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,875
AT THE END OF THIS
LONG STRAIGHTAWAY

235
00:15:41,958 --> 00:15:43,416
COMES A HAIRPIN TURN.

236
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:46,208
I'LL BE AT FULL THROTTLE,
READY TO MAKE MY MOVE.

237
00:15:46,291 --> 00:15:48,958
AND THE REST WILL BE HISTORY.

238
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:50,291
HERE IT COMES.

239
00:15:50,375 --> 00:15:52,625
I'M GONNA OUTRACE THIS KID
WITH MY TECHNIQUE ALONE.

240
00:15:52,708 --> 00:15:55,125
I DON'T NEED THE POWER
OF MY CAR TO WIN.

241
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:10,750
- HOLY CRAP! HE'S REALLY FAST!

242
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:12,958
THE FASTEST
I'VE EVER GONE UP AGAINST.

243
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:28,500
- THEY SHOULD BE HERE
ANY MINUTE.

244
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,875
- ( tires screeching )

245
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:33,958
- boy 2: LOOK! HERE THEY COME!

246
00:16:34,041 --> 00:16:36,625
THE LAN-EVO'S IN THE LEAD!
HE'S COMIN' IN FAST!

247
00:16:36,708 --> 00:16:39,250
- THIS IS THE BEST SEAT IN THE
HOUSE. AKINA'S FIVE HAIRPINS!

248
00:16:50,166 --> 00:16:51,916
- ( crowd cheers )

249
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,916
- MAN, WHAT INCREDIBLE POWER!

250
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,958
- YEAH, IT'S JUST LIKE A WORLD
RALLY CHAMPIONSHIP CAR!

251
00:16:57,041 --> 00:16:58,291
- ( tires screeching )

252
00:16:58,375 --> 00:17:00,416
- I CAN'T BELIEVE
HOW FAR BEHIND THE EIGHT-SIX IS!

253
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,958
I'VE SEEN ALMOST ALL HIS RACES

254
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:03,250
AND HE'S NEVER HAD
THIS MUCH GROUND

255
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,208
TO MAKE UP GOIN' INTO HAIRPINS.

256
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:07,208
- WHO KNOWS? MAYBE
THE EIGHT-SIX WON'T BE ABLE

257
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:08,791
TO PULL OFF A WIN THIS TIME.

258
00:17:08,875 --> 00:17:10,541
HIS CAR IS TOTALLY INFERIOR.

259
00:17:11,416 --> 00:17:13,250
THERE HE IS!

260
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:15,500
- IT'S TIME TO START
USING THE DITCH.

261
00:17:28,875 --> 00:17:30,958
- THAT WAS AWESOME!

262
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:33,458
- YEAH, I KNOW.
HOW DID HE TURN SO FAST?

263
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:36,666
- DID YA SEE THAT?

264
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:39,416
BUNTA'S SON WAS BEHIND THE
WHEEL OF THAT CAR.

265
00:17:40,458 --> 00:17:41,750
- YOU'RE KIDDIN' ME, RIGHT?

266
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:43,458
I MEAN, DAMN,
IF I DIDN'T KNOW ANY BETTER.

267
00:17:43,541 --> 00:17:44,625
I WOULD'VE ASSUMED THAT
IT WAS BUNTA

268
00:17:44,708 --> 00:17:45,875
STEERING THROUGH THAT CORNER.

269
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,833
JUST THE SOUND ALONE
SHOWS THE KIND OF TALENT

270
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:49,458
THAT KID REALLY HAS.

271
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:51,750
I SWEAR HE HAD TO HAVE REALLY
BEEN FLOORIN' THE PEDAL

272
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:53,291
THROUGHOUT MOST OF THAT DRIFT.

273
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:55,250
I'VE NEVER SEEN A TEENAGER
WITH THAT CALIBER OF SKILLS

274
00:17:55,333 --> 00:17:56,666
UNDER HIS BELT!

275
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,541
- WELL, THE APPLE DOESN'T FALL
TOO FAR FROM THE TREE.

276
00:17:58,625 --> 00:18:00,750
- YEAH, BUT
THAT SORT OF AGGRESSIVE DRIVING

277
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:04,000
CAN TEAR AN ENGINE TO PIECES
ALMOST AS IF IT WERE PAPER.

278
00:18:16,875 --> 00:18:19,375
- ( grunts ) DAMN,
THESE TURNS ARE A BITCH!

279
00:18:25,166 --> 00:18:28,541
I MAY HAVE LOST SOME TIME, BUT
NOT ENOUGH TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

280
00:18:28,625 --> 00:18:30,583
I DON'T CARE WHAT KIND OF CAR
YOU'RE IN,

281
00:18:30,666 --> 00:18:33,000
ANYONE WOULD LOSE SPEED
ON THESE TURNS.

282
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:38,333
NOW THAT I HAVE
SUCH A HUGE LEAD,

283
00:18:38,416 --> 00:18:41,000
IT SHOULD BE SMOOTH SAILIN'
ALL THE WAY TILL THE END.

284
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,416
WHAT THE...

285
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:49,583
- ♪ AS YOU KNOW, BABY,
STAY TONIGHT ♪

286
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:51,916
♪ SO HOLD ME IN YOUR ARMS ♪

287
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,416
♪ I LOVE YOU
LIKE YOU ARE, BABY ♪

288
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,833
- NO WAY! YOU'VE GOTTA BE
KIDDIN' ME!

289
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:58,166
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

290
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:01,875
♪ I WANNA SAY TO YOU,
LET ME SAY AGAIN ♪

291
00:19:01,958 --> 00:19:05,583
♪ I LOVE YOU
LIKE YOU ARE, BABY ♪

292
00:19:05,666 --> 00:19:08,000
♪ TONIGHT, BABY, HOLD ME ♪

293
00:19:08,083 --> 00:19:09,916
- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT!

294
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,166
I CAN'T EVEN SHAKE OFF
AN EIGHT-SIX?

295
00:19:12,250 --> 00:19:13,625
WITH ALL MY POWER
AND TECHNIQUE,

296
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:16,041
THIS RACE SHOULD
BE OVER ALREADY!

297
00:19:18,083 --> 00:19:21,291
YOU BASTARD.
I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU PASS ME!

298
00:19:31,041 --> 00:19:33,208
- THEY SHOULD BE HERE SOON.

299
00:19:33,291 --> 00:19:35,083
- SO I WONDER WHICH ONE'S
GONNA BE IN THE LEAD.

300
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:37,416
MAN, THE LAN-EVO
OR THE EIGHT-SIX?

301
00:19:40,041 --> 00:19:42,375
KEISUKE, YOU SAID THAT
IF THE LAN-EVO IS IN THE LEAD,

302
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:43,625
THEN HE'LL END
UP LOSING THE RACE,

303
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:45,916
BUT HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?

304
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,750
- THAT'S EASY. FROM
MY OWN PERSONAL EXPERIENCE.

305
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:51,416
NO MATTER WHAT YOU DO HE WON'T
LET YOU RUN AWAY WITH THE LEAD.

306
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:55,541
HE STICKS TO YOUR BUMPER
LIKE SUPER GLUE.

307
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:00,333
IF YOU LET HIM GET TO YOU
AND START RELYING ON POWER

308
00:20:00,416 --> 00:20:02,333
THEN YOUR TIRES WILL START
TO LOSE AIR PRESSURE.

309
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:09,625
- I CAN'T GET THIS PUNK
OFF MY ASS!

310
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:11,500
- THE KEY HERE IS HOW
YOU USE THE TIRES

311
00:20:11,583 --> 00:20:13,416
TO YOUR GREATEST ADVANTAGE.

312
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:17,125
ANYONE WHO JUMPS INTO THE LEAD
WITHOUT KNOWING THAT WILL LOSE.

313
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:24,958
- Seiji: MY FRONT TIRES
ARE LOSING PRESSURE.

314
00:20:26,416 --> 00:20:30,916
THIS RACE IS PISSING ME OFF.
I CAN'T STAY FOCUSED!

315
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,208
DON'T PANIC, THOUGH.
THERE'S NO NEED TO FREAK OUT.

316
00:20:35,291 --> 00:20:37,625
I CAN WIN THIS
AS LONG AS I KEEP MY LEAD.

317
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:40,666
I'M IN A BETTER POSITION
THAN HIM ANYWAY.

318
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:42,916
NO MATTER HOW FAST HE IS
IN THE TURNS,

319
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,916
HE STILL CAN'T GET
ENOUGH SPEED TO PASS ME

320
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,250
WHEN WE'RE OUT OF 'EM.

321
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:48,416
ONCE WE HIT THE LAST
STRAIGHTAWAY, I'M HOME FREE!

322
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:50,958
( sighs )

323
00:20:53,958 --> 00:20:55,375
I WAS RIGHT.

324
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:57,750
DITCHING SIMULATION THREE
AND TAKING THE LEAD BACK THERE

325
00:20:57,833 --> 00:21:01,125
WAS THE RIGHT MOVE.
I'VE WON THIS RACE, KYOICHI!

326
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:05,250
- ♪ I WANNA SAY TO YOU,
LET ME SAY AGAIN ♪

327
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:08,500
♪ I LOVE YOU
LIKE YOU ARE, BABY ♪

328
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:12,291
- ( theme song playing )

329
00:21:25,416 --> 00:21:27,333
- ( singing in Japanese )

330
00:23:10,250 --> 00:23:12,791
- Announcer: THE END IS NEAR!
WHAT DID TAKUMI DECIDE TO DO

331
00:23:12,875 --> 00:23:14,625
DURING HIS TOUGHEST
RACE YET?

332
00:23:14,708 --> 00:23:16,666
NEXT ON INITIAL D
SECOND STAGE.

333
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:18,458
- Takumi: HOLLOW VICTORY.

334
00:23:18,541 --> 00:23:19,833
- Announcer: DON'T MISS IT!

